        <T>  createOrGetChannel(java.lang.String name,
                            unit,
                           java.lang.String description)
        Creates a new channel or gets the one with the given name. The Channel must have a unit, and it can only contain values of a data type of the unit.
        Parameters:
        name - The channel name (mandatory, cannot be null)
        unit - Unit of the channel. Use predefined unit e.g. Unit.PERCENT or create your own with Unit.createCustomUnit(String name, Class dataType)
        description - a short description (optional, can be null)
        Returns:
        The new created channel or the one with the given name

      • createOrGetChannel

        <T>  createOrGetChannel(java.lang.String name,
                            unit,
                           java.lang.String description,
                           int r,
                           int g,
                           int b)
        * Creates a new channel or gets the one with the given name. The Channel must have a unit, and it can only contain values of a data type of the unit. Channel color will be always set to (r,g,b) values.
        Parameters:
        name - The channel name (mandatory, cannot be null)
        unit - Unit of the channel. Use predefined unit e.g. Unit.PERCENT or create your own with Unit.createCustomUnit(String name, Class dataType)
        description - a short description (optional, can be null)
        r - Red component of channel's color
        g - Green component of channel's color
        b - Blue component of channel's color
        Returns:
        The new created channel. Null if the channel already exists

        rgb - Array with length 3 that contains red, green and blue components of color

      • isValidFrancaTrace

        boolean isValidFrancaTrace(java.lang.String fullQualifiedInterface,
                         java.util.List<java.lang.String> trace)
        This method checks a given trace string (Format: MESSAGETYPE_MessageCallName, e.g. CALL_CreateLocationInput) against the Franca contract of a given interface name (full qualified name).
        Parameters:
        fullQualifiedInterface - The interface name (full qualified), which contains the Franca contract.
        trace - The communication message, that should be checked against the contract in the format MESSAGETYPE_MessageCallName).
        Returns:
        true, if this was a valid call and false otherwise.

      • plantUmlToSVG

        boolean plantUmlToSVG(java.lang.String plantUmlText,
                    java.lang.String pathToImage)
        Renders a Plant UML text as SVG image. Plant UML syntax is described here: http://plantuml.com
        Parameters:
        plantUmlText - Text that shall be rendered. Text must be correct Plant UML syntax, see http://plantuml.com
        pathToImage - Path to the rendered image. Be carefully, image is overridden if exists. Relative path is relative to EB solys executable folder.
        Returns:
        Returns true, if image was created successfully, false otherwise. If Plant UML syntax was wrong, image is still generated.

                    java.lang.String pathToImage)
        Renders a Plant UML text as PNG image. Plant UML syntax is described here: http://plantuml.com
        Parameters:
        plantUmlText - Text that shall be rendered. Text must be correct Plant UML syntax, see http://plantuml.com
        pathToImage - Path to the rendered image. Be carefully, image is overridden if exists. Relative path is relative to EB solys executable folder.
        Returns:
        Returns true, if image was created successfully, false otherwise. If Plant UML syntax was wrong, image is still generated.
